The paper deals with generative models for images, specifically GANs, and their applications in various tasks such as anomaly detection, domain adaptation, and adversarial defense. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also proposes a new technique for projecting images onto the manifold inferred by the generator, which involves approximating unknown corruptions at test time. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), graphics (cs.GR), and multimedia (cs.MM) categories, as these areas often deal with image processing and manipulation techniques.
